article.headline: TCU 88, Texas-Pan American 58
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Hank Thorns and Craig Williams scored 16 points apiece and TCU opened the game with an 18-0 run in an 88-58 victory over Texas-Pan American on Wednesday night. Garlon Green and Amric Fields added 14 each for the Horned Frogs (10-5), who made eight of their first 14 shots. Nate Butler had nine rebounds and Kyan Anderson seven assists for TCU, which has won two in a row and three of four. Brandon Provost and Aaron Urbanus scored 14 points each for the Broncs (5-15), losers of three straight and seven of eight. Provost had a game-high four 3-pointers as Texas-Pan American tumbled to 0-11 on the road. His 3-pointer got the Broncs on the board after 6:44 had elapsed. The Horned Frogs held a shooting edge of 52 percent to 37 percent and outrebounded the Broncs 41-30. TCU, which led 47-28 at halftime, is 6-0 against opponents from Texas.
